## Dependency Catalog

List every dependency once.

| ID               | Dependency | Class | Required Condition | Required For | Source Trace | Strictness | Planning Weight | Evidence Required | Status | Notes |
| ---------------- | ---------- | ----- | ------------------ | ------------ | ------------ | ---------- | --------------- | ----------------- | ------ | ----- |
| EVAL-DEP-001     | {{name}}   | {{Functional / Technical / Operational / Cross-Cutting}} | {{behavior_condition_or_process}} | {{run_pass_governance_evidence_safe_failure_or_condition}} | {{eval_id_section_or_line}} | {{strictness}} | {{weight}} | {{evidence}} | {{status_or_Not_Assessed}} | {{upstream_downstream_blocking_or_TBD}} |

Rules:

* Use one row per atomic dependency.
* Do not create separate crosswalks, coverage matrices, dependency graphs, or gate matrices that restate the same relationships.
* Put relationship details in `Required For`, `Source Trace`, and `Notes`.
* Use `Class` to distinguish functional, technical, operational, and cross-cutting dependencies.
* Split cross-cutting dependencies when the functional, technical, and operational parts can be evidenced or remediated separately.
* Technical dependencies must describe necessary technical conditions, not preferred implementation designs.
* Operational dependencies must describe executable run, maintenance, evidence-retention, reporting, or automated gate conditions without inventing owners.
* Do not list forbidden non-implementation artifacts or policy-mediated artifacts as dependency rows.
* Do list implementation-aligned machine-required artifacts when they are consumed, produced, compared, retained, validated, or queried by executable evals.
* Remap non-implementation obligations to their executable checks, machine-verifiable evidence, runtime metadata, generated report data, validation hooks, or result aggregation dependencies.

