## Specialized Requirements

List only source-defined items that need dedicated handling beyond the main dependency row.

| ID                           | Type | Required Item | Requirement | Required By | Evidence / Verification | Failure Risk | Source Trace | Status |
| ---------------------------- | ---- | ------------- | ----------- | ----------- | ---------------- | ------------ | ------------ | ------ |
| EVAL-DEP-SPECIALIZED-001     | {{Evidence / Fixture / Input / Generated Report / Runtime Artifact / Negative Control / Stability / Public Metadata / Schema or Validation / Conditional}} | {{item}} | {{requirement}} | {{eval_or_requirement}} | {{evidence_or_TBD}} | {{risk_or_TBD}} | {{source_trace}} | {{status_or_Not_Assessed}} |

Use this section for:

* fixtures, corpora, inputs, scenarios, and datasets
* fixture manifests and machine-consumed eval input artifacts
* generated eval reports, report fields, machine-verifiable evidence packages, and machine-produced summary outputs
* evidence that must be produced, retained, linked, reported, or machine-verified
* static scan outputs, replay records, comparison artifacts, capability fingerprints, and negative-control outputs
* negative controls and safe-failure behavior
* determinism, replay, reproducibility, regression, stability, or baseline requirements
* runtime/queryable public, external, support, capability, compliance, or disclosure metadata requirements
* machine-checkable schema, ontology, model-change, relationship validation, identity-domain, public-contract, compatibility, or validation mechanisms
* source-defined conditional requirements

Do not list forbidden non-implementation artifacts or policy-mediated artifacts in this section.
Do not list those source obligations anywhere else in the output.
Do list implementation-aligned machine-required artifacts when they meet the specialized requirements criteria.

If no specialized requirements are defined, write:

```text
No specialized dependency requirements are defined by the eval specs.
```

