## Completeness Checklist

Before finalizing this dependency inventory, verify:

* Every file under `.agents/evals/` was considered.
* Every included eval source appears in the Source Inventory.
* Every eval ID or suite ID is represented or marked `TBD`.
* Every required check is represented by dependencies.
* Every pass criterion is represented by dependencies.
* Every fail criterion is reflected in failure, negative-control, or false-success dependencies.
* Every blocked or inconclusive condition is reflected in run, evidence, result aggregation, or governance evidence dependencies.
* Every fixture, corpus, input, scenario, or dataset requirement is represented.
* Every fixture artifact, fixture manifest, or other machine-consumed eval input artifact is represented when required.
* Every generated report or machine-verifiable report artifact requirement is represented as an implementation-first dependency.
* Every required report field is represented or summarized without loss.
* Every evidence requirement is represented.
* Every negative control is represented.
* Every required scan output, replay record, comparison artifact, capability fingerprint, or negative-control output is represented.
* Every deterministic, replay, reproducibility, regression, or stability requirement is represented.
* Every runtime/queryable public, external, support, capability, compliance, or disclosure metadata requirement is represented as an implementation-first dependency.
* Every machine-checkable schema, ontology, model-change, relationship validation, identity-domain, public-contract, compatibility, or validation mechanism is represented as an implementation-first dependency.
* Every source-defined minimum bar is decomposed into implementation-first dependencies or omitted from output.
* Every source requirement that names a policy-mediated non-implementation artifact is remapped to implementation-first dependencies or omitted from output.
* Every explicit non-pass condition is represented.
* Each catalog row has an explicit dependency class.
* Technical dependencies do not prescribe implementation design unless the eval requires it.
* Operational dependencies are not omitted.
* No dependency catalog row or specialized requirement row has a forbidden non-implementation artifact as its primary deliverable.
* No section, table, list, evidence field, status field, summary count, or open question emits policy-mediated artifacts.
* No implementation-aligned machine-required artifact is omitted merely because it is an artifact.
* Shared dependencies are consolidated without losing source traceability.
* Conditional dependencies include their conditions.
* Ambiguities are recorded in Open Dependency Questions.
* Repository satisfaction status is `Not Assessed` unless explicitly requested.
* No roadmap appears.
* No actual epics appear.
* No actual milestones appear.
* No implementation tasks appear.
* No architecture is invented.
* No evaluation result or policy-mediated status is claimed.
* The inventory is detailed enough to drive downstream roadmap, epic, milestone, and remediation planning.
